[{"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion M\u00fcnster S-2230 - 68 - St 11 - 31bek"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "OFD D\u00fcsseldorf S-2230 A - St 112 from 01021982S-2230 -S-2230EStG: 13EStG: 13aOFD M\u00fcnster S-2221 - 11 - St 16 - 31 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "11 3 1983OFD M\u00fcnster S-2230 - 79 - St 16 - 31 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "8 7 1983OFD M\u00fcnster S-2230 - 79 - St 16 - 31 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "23 12 1983 Income tax assessment of farmers and foresters for the assessment period 1980 Reference: Circular decree dated 27 7 1981 - S-2230 - 68 - St 11 - 31 -1 Annex: Examples for calculating the value of work (Section 13a (5) EStG) 1 General2 Determination of profit from agriculture and forestry according to average rates (\u00a7 13a EStG) 21 Scope of application211 On \u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 No. 2 EStG (initial value limit) 212 On \u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 (livestock limit) 22 Determination of profits221 Basic amount222 Value of work223 Rent received224 Profits according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 8 of the Income Tax Act2241 Sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals2242 Vegetable growing (horticultural use) 2243 Fruit growing (horticultural use) 225 Value in use of the apartment226 Lease interest, debt interest, ongoing burdens227 Other additions and reductions3 Determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry by comparing operating income with operating expenses (Section 4 (3) EStG) 31 area of \u200b\u200bapplication ich32 Determination of profits (Section 17 EStR) 321 Average livestock values322 Value in use of the apartment4 Determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry through accounting (Section 4 (1) EStG) 41 Scope of application42 Accounting43 Profit determination431 Average livestock values \u200b\u200b(Section 125 EStR) 432 Value in use of the apartment5 Estimate of the profit for agriculture and Foresters whose profit cannot be determined according to average rates5 1 General52 Estimation of profit according to standard rates521 Starting amount522 Lease income523 Surcharges for profits or income not paid for with the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits5231 Sale of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals5232 Above normal animal husbandry5233 Field vegetable cultivation5234 Vegetable cultivation (horticultural use) 5235 Fruit cultivation (horticultural use) 524 Use value of the apartment525 Wage expenses526 Lease expenses, debt interest, permanent burdens527 Other surcharges and reductions5271 Appreciation due to \u00a75 special additions and reductions5271 76 EStDV6 Miscellaneous61 Retirement benefits62 Control reports63 Unit value reports64 Use of the valuation files when carrying out the assessment1 General When assessing income tax for farmers and foresters for the year 1980, the effects of the law on the new regulation of income taxation in agriculture and forestry of 25 June 1980 (BStBl IS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "400) must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The following instructions are based on the EStR taking into account the ESt\u00c4R 1981 (BStBl 1981 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "779) reference"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Details of the changes in the determination of profits and the accounting obligation, the benefits for the sale of certain agricultural and forestry operations (\u00a7 14a EStG) and the newly introduced tax reduction for income from agriculture and forestry (\u00a7 34e EStG) can be found in the introductory letter of the BMF of 27 3 1981 (BStBl IS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "282)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "2 Determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry according to average rates (\u00a7 13a EStG) 21 Scope In addition to Section 127 Paragraphs 3 - 10 EStR and No. 2 of the introductory letter, reference is made to the following: 211 Regarding \u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 No. 2 EStG (initial value limit) is decisive the initial value determined in accordance with Section 13a (4) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Cattle surcharges can therefore not be taken into account as long as they have not been made the subject of a value update by the valuation body in accordance with \u00a7\u00a7 41 in conjunction with 22 para. 1 no. 1 BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Something else only applies if the requirements of Section 13a Paragraph 4 No. 1 Sentence 4 EStG are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "212 Regarding \u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 (animal population limit) For the calculation of the animal population limit of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 EStG, I refer to Section 127 Paragraph 7 EStR, Item 22 of the introductory letter and No. 3 of my circular of 21 May 1981 - S-2230 - 63 - St 11 - 3122 Determination of profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In detail, I would like to point out the following: 221 Basic amount When determining the basic amount according to Section 13a Paragraph 4 EStG, Section 130a Paragraph 3 EStR must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "222 Value of the work performance In the case of the basic amount according to Section 13a (4) EStG, it is assumed that the business is managed exclusively with paid workers (see Section 36 (2) BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The value of the work performed by the business owner and his relatives who are not employed in the company on the basis of an employment relationship to be determined in accordance with Section 13a (5) EStG must therefore be added to the basic amount (Section 13a (3) No. 2 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Section 130a, Paragraphs 4 to 6 EStR must be observed here"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In detail, the following is pointed out: When determining the value of the work performance for the physical cooperation of the business owner and the relatives who are not employed, only the work performance is to be taken into account in the result, which is based on the area recorded in the initial value according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 4 EStG in the individual case not applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The paid workers are to be counted towards the appropriate number of VAK according to the duration of their employment (\u00a7 13a Abs 5 Nr 5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to temporary workers employed on a short-term basis, as well as to workers who have been made available by contractors for certain ordering, maintenance or harvesting work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "For the crediting of the paid VAK"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "a breakdown of the wages is necessary, provided that it is attributable to the uses contained in the initial value (Section 13a Paragraph 4 EStG) and to the uses not contained therein"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Make Stpfl in the tax return (form \"Annex L\") to the extent / proportion of their employment or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "the activities of other people (relatives, third parties) in the company or no or obviously incorrect information on the part of the work attributable to special uses, the (physical) work or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "the proportion of the work performed by the business owner, the relatives employed in the business and / or the remunerated workers, if applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "with the assistance of the responsible ALS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "To determine the share that is attributable to special uses, the Felsmann comment in section C 27 (p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "523) serve as a guide on the average labor requirement in special branches of business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "See Appendix for examples of calculating the value of work done"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "223 Rental interest received Reference is made to Section 13a (6) sentence 2 EStG and Section 130a (7) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The rent received also includes income from ground rent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Income from hunting leases is compensated by the basic amount as it relates to areas included in the initial value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "224 Profits according to Section 13a Paragraph 8 EStG I refer to Section 130a Paragraph 8 EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In addition, please note the following: Profits from operations that were not taken into account when determining the initial value are e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits from sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals (see section 2241), profits from renting rooms to holiday guests and from renting camping sites (ESt-Kartei NW \u00a7\u00a7 13 13a EStG A No. 82), interest income, insofar as the capital claim The business assets include profits from riding schools and rental of own horses, as far as it is income from agriculture and forestry, profits from secondary activities, profits from investments that belong to the agricultural and forestry business assets, profits from the rearing of animals in the wage system"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Profits from the cross-company use of machines, which are achieved in the context of agriculture and forestry, are not to be recorded according to Section 13a (8) No. 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "You have already been paid for by applying the basic amount (ESt-Kartei NW \u00a7\u00a7 13 13a EStG A Nr 103)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The profits (additional profits) according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 8 EStG are basically to be determined by comparing the operating income and operating expenses (\u00a7 4 Paragraph 3 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If no records are available, the profits (additional profits) are to be estimated according to the principles of Section 4 Paragraph 1 EStG (Section 130a Paragraph 8 Sentences 8 - 11 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "When estimating the profits (additional profits) from sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals as well as from vegetable growing and intensive fruit growing in the context of horticultural use, the following guidelines can serve as a guide"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Their application must not lead to an obviously incorrect taxation (see judgment of the BFH of 16 12 1965 BStBl 1966 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "193)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "2241 Sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals As additional profit from the sale of breeding animals and other particularly valuable animals, 80%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "of the amount by which the sales proceeds exceed the following starting values \u200b\u200b(normal prices): Breeding bulls 2700 DM Breeding cows 2300 DM Breeding cattle 2100 DM Breeding boars550 DM Breeding sows 750 DM For breeding and riding horses, the additional profit is 60 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "the amount by which the selling price exceeds the initial value of 3000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If sales proceeds of more than DM 13,000 are achieved, the full amount of DM 7,000 (DM 3,000 + 40%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "of 10,000 DM)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Wages for paid workers are taken into account here, so they cannot be set separately in this respect"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "2242 Vegetable growing (horticultural use) To distinguish vegetable growing (horticultural use) from vegetable growing within the framework of agricultural use, see Sections 108, Paragraph 2 and 607, Paragraph 1, No. 1 BewRL 1964.If vegetable growing is included in agricultural use, a surcharge is made in accordance with Section 13a, Paragraph 8 EStG not considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Vegetables are only grown in the context of agricultural use if headed cabbage (white cabbage, red cabbage and savoy cabbage), picking peas and picking beans are grown exclusively using agricultural cultivation methods as part of the agricultural crop rotation as the main crop"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, the types of cabbage mentioned and or peas or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Do not alternate beans with other agricultural crops such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Wheat, rye, barley, oats or beets, but one after the other or alternately with the same or different types of vegetables (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Endive, lettuce, lamb's lettuce, spinach, carrots, celery, beetroot, onions, radishes, leeks, tomatoes, kohlrabi cucumbers, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": ") cultivated, the cultivation is no longer part of the agricultural crop rotation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "It is then rather about vegetable growing (horticultural use)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In the case of vegetable growing (horticultural use), income fluctuates between DM 15,000 and DM 80,000 per hectare"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "You are dependent on z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "of soil quality, irrigation possibilities, under glass areas, number of harvests"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The net profit can be 40 to 65 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "of revenues are estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The profit is influenced by the type of marketing (auction in wholesale, sale from the farm, sale at the weekly market) and the wage expenditure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "When growing vegetables without a covered growing area or with covered growing areas up to 3 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "of the total vegetable growing area, the profit can also be estimated according to the number of unpaid family workers fully employed in vegetable growing as follows: with a vegetable growing area up to 2 ha 16,000 DM / FAK with a vegetable growing area of \u200b\u200b2 to 4 ha 22,000 DM / FAK with a vegetable growing area over 4 ha 38,000 DM / FAK This estimation method is particularly suitable for cases in which the operating income has not been specified or has obviously been incomplete"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "An accurate estimate in individual cases is usually possible in close cooperation with the ALS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "2243 Fruit growing (horticultural use) The income fluctuates between 15,000 and 35,000 DM per hectare"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "They depend on the quality of the soil, climate and the age structure of the orchard"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The net profit can be 30 to 50 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "of revenues are estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The profit is influenced by the type of marketing (sale in the wholesale market, sale from the farm, sale on the weekly market) and the wage expenditure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "No. 2242 last paragraph applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "225 Value in use of the apartment The apartment i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 7 EStG includes the buildings and parts of buildings that serve the owner of the business, the family members belonging to his household and the retirees for residential purposes (\u00a7 34 Paragraph 3 BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If the residential rights of the senior citizen are secured in rem, the value of the apartment is to be reduced proportionally - according to the ratio of the living space provided to the total living space"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In this case, a deduction of the value of the rented apartment as special expenses (permanent burden) is not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "226 Lease interest paid, interest on debt, ongoing charges Reference is made to Section 13a (3) sentence 2 EStG and Section 130a (9) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Interest subsidies from public funds reduce the deductible debt interest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "227 Other additions and reductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The following can be considered: Additions and deductions according to \u00a7 6c EStG, increased deductions for residential buildings according to \u00a7\u00a7 7b, 54 EStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 52 EStDV, tax relief according to \u00a7 78 EStDV In the case of increased deductions according to \u00a7\u00a7 7b, 54 EStG, it should be noted that the loss clause of \u00a7 7a Paragraph 6 EStG for financial years beginning after December 31, 1979 has been removed (\u00a7 52 Par 20a EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "However, the tax relief according to \u00a7 78 EStDV may still not lead to a loss from agriculture and forestry (see \u00a7 78 Paragraph 3 EStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The increased deductions according to \u00a7 7d EStG, \u00a7\u00a7 82a, 82g and 82i EStDV and according to the Protective Building Act cannot be taken into account when determining profits according to \u00a7 13a Paragraphs 2 to 7 EStG, because the average rates are used to replace the depreciation and thus also the depreciation increase deductions are generally compensated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "However, if an asset is used in a part of the business whose full income is to be recorded in accordance with Section 13a (8) EStG, increased deductions can also be taken into account when determining the profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "3 Determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry by comparing the operating income with the operating expenses (Section 4 Paragraph 3 EStG) 31 Scope of application Reference is made to Section 127 Paragraph 3 EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "32 Determination of profits (Section 17 EStR) In this regard, I would like to point out the following: 321 Average livestock values"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Section 125a EStR, under certain conditions, can also be used when determining profits in accordance with Section 4 (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "For the rest, I refer to Section 431322 Value in Use of the Apartment Section 225 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "To determine the value in use of the apartment, reference is made to the ESt-Kartei NW \u00a7\u00a7 13 13a EStG A No. 100"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the value in use is to be measured according to the circumstances of the individual case, even for farmers and foresters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "4 Determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry through bookkeeping (Section 4 Paragraph 1 EStG) 41 Scope of application Reference is made to Section 127 Paragraph 1 EStR and No. 5 of the introductory letter"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Cattle surcharges are also to be taken into account when determining the economic value limit according to \u00a7 141 Paragraph 1 No. 3 AO if they have not yet been the subject of a value update according to \u00a7\u00a7 41 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "V with 22 para 1 no 1 BewG have been made"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "42 Bookkeeping On section 13 EStR and the letter of the BMF dated December 15, 1981 (BStBl 1981 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "878) is pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "43 Determination of profit 431 Average livestock values \u200b\u200b(Section 125 EStR) The applicable average livestock values \u200b\u200bresult from the ESt card index NW \u00a7\u00a7 13 13a EStG A No. 20 For the evaluation of horses from the 1980/1981 business year I refer additionally to the order of 22 6 1981 - S- 2132a - 2 - St 11 - 31 out (ESt- Kartei NW \u00a7\u00a7 13 13a EStG A Nr 111)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "432 Value in use of the apartment Section 322 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "5 Estimation of the profit for farmers and foresters whose profit is not to be determined according to average rates5 1 General For farmers and foresters whose profit is not to be determined according to average rates (Section 13a EStG) but according to Section 4 (1) EStG, but which are subject to their obligation to keep books or do not comply properly, the profit is to be estimated in individual cases according to \u00a7 162 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to those farmers and foresters who are neither obliged to keep accounts nor meet the requirements of Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 2 and 3 EStG if they do not keep books within the meaning of Section 4 Paragraph 1 EStG and also the operating income and Have not recorded business expenses within the meaning of Section 4 Paragraph 3 EStG (Section 127 Paragraph 2-4 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The estimate has - with the exception of the in Section 127 Paragraph 4 S."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "6, second half-sentence of the EStR - to be carried out in accordance with the principles of Section 4 (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "When making the estimate, all circumstances of the individual case that are important for the estimate must be taken into account (Section 162 (1) sentence 2 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The aim of the estimate must be to determine the profit actually achieved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The uncertainties inherent in an estimate are, however, at the expense of the taxpayer, who himself gave cause for the estimate by neglecting his tax cooperation obligations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In the case of an estimate of the profit, in cases where there is a bookkeeping obligation, the investment must always be made, and in the remaining cases if the basis for the estimate is not sufficiently reliable, subject to review (Section 164 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "For VZ 1980, the following explanatory text must be included in the notification or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "to be attached as an attachment: \"The profit from agriculture and forestry was for the financial year 19"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "/ 19th"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Estimated according to \u00a7 162 AO because you have not declared your winnings, although you are obliged to keep accounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If you actually achieved a higher profit than the estimated, the tax would have been set too low"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In this case, there may be tax evasion or frivolous tax reduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "You can then, however, by declaring the profit actually achieved under the further requirements of \u00a7\u00a7 371 378 Paragraph 3 AO punitive or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Obtain no fines"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Furthermore, I would like to point out that failure to comply with the accounting obligation can already result in a tax risk"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "\"52 Estimation of the profit according to standard rates Which estimation method is to be used in the individual case is left to the discretion of the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If, in individual cases, an estimation method tailored to the particular operational conditions is not to be preferred, or if the accounting results of comparable operations or empirical data are not available, the profit must be estimated as follows in accordance with the principles of Section 4 (1) EStG: Starting amount (Section 521) Lease income (Sect 522) Surcharges for winnings that are not settled with the starting amount or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits (Sect. 523) Value in use of the apartment (Sect. 524)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Wage expenses (Section 525)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Lease expenses, debt interest, permanent burdens (Sect. 526)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "other surcharges and reductions (section 527) = profit for the financial year The following guide rates are intended as a guide for an accurate estimate of the profit (section 127 paragraph 2 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "2 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "At the same time, a reduction in the estimated profit due to objections to individual points in the valuation process is generally out of the question because special circumstances in an individual branch of the business do not allow any conclusions to be drawn about the profit of the entire business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The application of the standard rates must not lead to an obviously incorrect taxation (see judgment of the BFH of 16 12 1965 BStBl 1966 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "193)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "When estimating the profit according to the guideline rates, the following must be observed in detail: 521 Starting amount The starting amount per hectare of usable agricultural area (UAA) for the 1980/81 business year is:"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "the LM) with a root crop portion of a) 15%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "and more of the LN1350 DMb) less than 15 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "the LN1250 DM2 for mixed farms (grassland share 31 to 70 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "der LN) with a root crop portion of a) 15%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "and more of the LN1250 DMb) less than 15 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "the LN1200 DM3 in pasture farming (grassland share 71%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "and more of the LN) 1200 DM4 For sugar beet farms (root crop content more than 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "of the LN, including: sugar beet content more than 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "der LN) 1900 DM Only the pure agricultural production areas belong to the agricultural use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Areas for buildings, courtyards, paths, ditches, field borders, water, land, quarries, sand pits, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Areas are therefore not considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Areas for house gardens are also not included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise, Section 124a Paragraph 3 EStR applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "For the calculation of the relevant root crop, grassland or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The proportion of sugar beet depends on the extent of this proportion in the respective marketing year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The areas under cultivation of root crops do not include those areas on which root crops are only grown as catch crops or as catch crops"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In the district of the tax offices of Arnsberg, Brilon, L\u00fcdenscheid, Meschede, Olpe and Siegen, a discount of up to (maximum) 30% from the starting amount can be made on request for companies whose areas are predominantly more than 250 m high, if the average RPS des Operation is less than 25 and, in addition, particularly unfavorable earnings ratios (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "due to waterlogging, steep slope)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "These requirements must always be checked by the ALS before the application is accepted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "522 Lease income Lease income, ground rent and hunting leases, reduced by proportionate operating expenses, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Property taxes are to be added to the starting amount if they are included in income from agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "This is the case when the leased or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Hereditary assets belong to the lessor's agricultural and forestry business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "523 Surcharges for winnings or winnings not settled with the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "All profits from sustainable or one-off operating income that are not included in the starting amount are to be added to the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Such surcharges come z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Consideration for additional profits from sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals, profits from abnormal animal husbandry, additional profits from special crops, profits from other special branches of business, profits from the removal and sale of land (see also - special operating income - on page 4 of Annex L)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The surcharges are generally to be determined by comparing the operating income and operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If no records are available, the profits (additional profits) are to be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The following guidelines can serve as a guide: 5231 Sale of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals Section 2241 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "5232 Abnormal animal husbandry Profits from animal breeding and husbandry are settled with the starting amount (Section 521), provided that the average normal animal population is not exceeded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "As animal husbandry paid for with the starting amount, for the area of \u200b\u200bthe regional tax office in M\u00fcnster, other farms up to 20 ha LN16 VE / ha14 VE / ha over 20 to 30 ha LN14 VE / ha12 VE / ha over 30 to 50 ha LN12 VE / ha10 VE / haover 50 ha LN10 VE / ha08 VE / haFodder holdings are holdings where the forage area is 60 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "and more of the usable agricultural area without courtyard and building space, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "matters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In this context, the forage area includes: Meadows (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Tree meadows, litter meadows), cattle pastures and fields, as well as the cultivation areas for clover in pure seed and mixed cultivation, clover grass, alfalfa, seradella, sainfoin, green corn, vetches, sweet lupins and all other forage plants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Areas on which grain is grown for body production are not included in the forage area even if the grain is fed to the livestock kept on the farm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "When calculating the number of animals and converting them into livestock units (VE), the procedure is in accordance with Section 124a (2) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Care must be taken that no animals are recorded twice"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "For the excess stock remaining after the normal stock has been taken into account, the following is to be set as profit for the 1980/81 financial year: As a rule, 300 DM per VE, with exclusive rearing of fattening poultry, 220 DM per VE"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If laying hens are kept exclusively, a surcharge of DM 420 per VE can be applied if the eggs are mainly sold to wholesalers and collection points"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The amounts deviating from the standard rate can also be used as a guide if the animals are kept predominantly by the aforementioned animals"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Wages are not taken into account here, so they can still be set separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "5233 Field vegetable cultivation Field vegetable cultivation is understood to mean the cultivation of vegetables according to agricultural cultivation methods within the framework of agricultural crop rotation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "A distinction must be made between field vegetable cultivation in annual cultivation and field vegetable cultivation as a replica"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Additional profit not settled with the starting amount (section 521) is to be set for the 1980/81 financial year: For field vegetable cultivationa) in annual cultivation: 7,000 DM per hectare minus the amount per hectare for this area set in the starting amount for this area) as a replica 5,000 DM per ha (excluding Reduction)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "It is up to the Stpfl to prove the actual proceeds from the field vegetable cultivation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, a discount of 25 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "be acknowledged"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The remaining amount is only to be reduced in the case of field vegetable cultivation in annual cultivation by the amount per hectare of lan used in the starting amount for this area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The above standard rates do not take into account wages and can therefore be deducted separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "5234 Vegetable growing (horticultural use) Section 2242 applies accordingly to the determination of profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "As a surcharge on the starting amount, however, only the additional profit, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "the profit reduced by the pro-rata starting amount applied in the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "5235 Fruit growing (horticultural use) Section 2243 applies accordingly to the determination of profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "As a surcharge on the starting amount, however, only the additional profit, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "the profit reduced by the pro-rata starting amount applied in the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "524 Value in use of the apartment Section 225 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "When estimating the profit, the gross value in use must always be applied, because the expenses associated with the apartment - with the exception of interest on debt (Section 526) and the increased deductions (Section 527) - are taken into account when determining the starting amounts (Section 521) and are thus compensated are"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "525 Wage expenses The starting amount (Section 521) is based on the assumption that the company is managed exclusively with unpaid workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Wage expenses are therefore to be deducted from the starting amount insofar as they relate to the profits settled with the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The treatment of wage expenses incurred with profits or income not paid for in the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits (see Sect. 523) result from the respective surcharge regulations (see Sections 5231 to 5235)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "For the distribution of wage expenses required in individual cases, Sect. 222 Nos. 2 and 3 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The wage expenses to be deducted also include the expenses for short-term temporary workers as well as for the workers who are"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Contractors have been made available for certain ordering, maintenance or harvesting work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If wage expenses in connection with machine expenses are invoiced in one sum by contractors, there are generally no concerns that the proportionate wage expenses to be taken into account at 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "appreciate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If wage expenses cannot be proven, an estimate e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "possible according to documents from comparable companies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Because of the need to notify the income tax office in such cases, please refer to section 62 lit."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "c) pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "526 Lease expenses, debt interest, permanent charges These expenses can be deducted if they are operating expenses and have not already been taken into account when determining the surcharges according to Sect. 523"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "If the lessee bears other expenses related to the leased property (e.g. rental fees) in addition to the interest for the leasing of land and / or buildings (net lease)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Property tax, apportionment of the Chamber of Agriculture, building insurance), these expenses are not deductible as business expenses, as they have already been taken into account when determining the starting amounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "527 Other surcharges and reductions 527 Allocation due to building depreciation in the case of profit estimation When calculating the starting amount, the deductions for wear and tear from the value of the business buildings are taken into account in accordance with \u00a7 7 EStG, because it is assumed that the business is managed by the owner himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In cases of leasing or free transfer of agricultural operations as a whole, the depreciation for the company buildings is available to the lessor or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "to the leaving farmer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "For this reason, the authorized user (manager of the business) must increase the starting amount (section 521) by DM 100 per hectare of leased land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "5272 Increased reductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "increased deductions for residential buildings according to \u00a7\u00a7 7b, 54 EStG and increased deductions according to \u00a7\u00a7 82a, 82g and 82i EStDV into consideration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "These increased deductions are, however, by the depreciation already taken into account in the starting amount according to \u00a7 7 Abs 4 EStG of 2 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "to shorten"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "When claiming higher deductions, it should be noted that the loss clause of \u00a7 7a Paragraph 6 EStG no longer applies for financial years beginning after December 31, 1979 (\u00a7 52 Paragraph 20a EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "5273 Special depreciation according to \u00a7 76 EStDV Special depreciation according to \u00a7 76 EStDV can be deducted from the starting amount if the register is kept according to \u00a7 7a Paragraph 8 EStG (cf. order of 8 5 1981 - S-2184 - 59 - St 11 - 31)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In these cases I would ask you to request the directory and to take a copy of the tax files"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "After the beneficial period of three financial years has expired, the starting amount is to be increased by a surcharge when claiming the preferential treatment according to \u00a7 76 EStDV, since according to \u00a7 76 paragraph 1 sentence 2 EStDV the residual value is the assessment basis for the further deductions for wear and tear and by applying the starting amount otherwise too high depreciation amounts would be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The surcharge for a financial year results from the sum of the special depreciation granted divided by the remaining useful life of the respective asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The initial amount must be increased for the remaining period of use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "When using the preferential treatment for immovable assets with a useful life of more than 30 years as well as for conversions and extensions of these assets, a correction is not necessary in view of Section 76 (4) sentence 3 EStDV for reasons of simplification"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In order to ensure that the surcharges are also taken into account in future assessments, the directory must be provided with a corresponding note and attached to the income tax file"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Section 5272 (2) applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "6 Other 61 Partial retirement benefits Sections 123 Paragraph 3 and 167 EStR as well as the circular dated 27 12 1976 - S-2221 - 11 - St 11 - 31 - are referred to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Evidence of cash and cashless partial retirement benefits must be provided"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, the value of the cashless partial retirement benefits can be recognized without special proof"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Assessment period 1980 For meals - with an elderly divider 2300 DM - with an elderly married couple 4100 DM For heating and lighting 400 DM62 Control messages Except in the usual cases (control messages for the purposes of the Bp, the recording of taxable transactions with other taxpayers, the inheritance tax), control messages are to be prepared in the following cases in particular: The responsible valuation body are the ones resulting from the declarations of the taxpayer or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "to disclose circumstances arising from the files that may affect the level of the fixed unit values \u200b\u200b(e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Change in areas for special uses, changes in animal populations - see also Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "from 10 6 1976 - S-2230 - 45 - St 11 - 31)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Information that may be of importance for an award according to \u00a7 41 BewG is summarized on page 4 of Annex L 1980"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "I therefore ask in all cases in which the livestock declared in Annex L obviously exceeds or exceeds the animal population customary in the area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "in which, for other reasons, a surcharge according to \u00a7 41 BewG may be considered, the assessment body can be informed by sending a copy of page 4 of Annex L."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Are access or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Leases known, so the lessor or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Inform the leaseholder of the competent assessment office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to the transfer of use free of charge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "It can be proceeded in accordance with No. 3 of the order of 27 1 1981 S-2230 - 63 - St 11 - 31"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "For the rest, I ask you to ensure that the taxpayers on page 2 of Annex L the address of the lessee / lessor, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "specify exactly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "In particular, cases without signal \"A\", in which wage expenses are claimed, and cases with significant wage expenses are to be reported to the responsible income tax office for examination by the income tax field audit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if wage expenses are set at an estimated amount when determining the profit (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "Section 525 Paragraph 4)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "63 Standard value notifications Unit value notifications for agricultural and forestry assets must always be evaluated promptly, particularly because of the possible effects on the way in which the taxpayer's profit is determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "64 Consultation of the valuation files when carrying out the assessment In particular when determining profits in accordance with Section 13a of the Income Tax Act (EStG) and in valuation cases, I ask that you refer to the assessment files for the assessment and review of the values \u200b\u200bto be applied in the individual case when calculating profits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "The system was not included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0022808.xml"}, "text": "--- Income tax / wage tax / church tax North Rhine-Westphalia agriculture"}]